About OS.js:
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
JavaScript Desktop Environment. For more information please visit the homepage.

For requirements, installation etc. see the INSTALL file.
For developer information, see the README.developer file
For HTML version of this document, see the README.markup file.

Applications etc.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
All Packages come separately. See the INSTALL files on how to obtain and install
the default set.

Features and Highlights (OUTDATED):
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Follows strict coding standards, fully documented
* Uses HTML5 and CSS2+ features (Supported features are detected on first run.)
* Uses a light-weight PHP backend
* Lazy-loading of resources (on-demand loading to reduce bandwidth usage upon startup)
* Simple process managment (process stack, kill processes etc)
* Desktop environment (Customizable settings, themes, fonts, cursors etc)
* Window Managment (With standard window actions like maximize, minimize, restore, on-top and so on)
* Session Managment (Save/Restore local[Storage], Create snapshots on server (for backup))
* Locales (Manage date/time, timezones and languages).
* Desktop Panels (movable)
* Desktop Panel items (See list below)
* Sandboxed Applications with API access and crash-handling
* Uses WebStorage to store system/user/application settings and sessions (Sessions can also be saved on server (including snapshots))
* TCP/IP Socket connections via WebSocket wrapper (hybi-00 and hybi-10)
* Application Compiler (Compiles Application+Glade-XML into JavaScript, CSS and PHP code, also minifies the code)
* VFS - Virtual Filesystem support (Block devices, Network connections, Compressed files etc. File-Alteration monitoring)
* Application WebWorkers for faster processing of complex data
* Server-Side libraries: Database, JSON, IMAP/SMTP, VFS-Operations, Misc helper functions/classes
* Common interactive dialogs:
  * Dialog: Font and Color Picker
  * Dialog: File Open, Save, Copy, Upload (HTML5)
  * Dialog: Lauch Application
  * Dialog: Modify Panel/PanelItem
  * Dialog: Confirm, Input and Message Boxes

